Name: FATAL_V12
Description: V_12P0 not available / not detected / timeout. -> Check short on V_12P0, check powersupply, check V_EXT (R5R20, R5R19), check PSU_V12P0_EN (R9A2, R9B2)

Name: FATAL_V5
Description: V_5P0 not available / timeout. -> Check short on V_5P0, check U3E2, Q3E1, Q3E2 and surrounding resistors.

Name: FATAL_PWRGPA
Description: PWRGPA timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_3P3, V_SOC1P8PLL, VMEMIOAB/CD, VTT[ABCD]. Pull VREG_PWRGPA_EN to V_3P3STBY manually and check V_3P3, V_SOC1P8PLL, VMEMIOAB/CD, (VTT[ABCD]) voltages.

Name: FATAL_PWRGPB
Description: PWRGPB timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE, V_MEMCORE. Pull VREG_PWRGPB_EN to V_3P3STBY manually and check V_FUSE, V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE, V_MEMCORE voltages.

Name: FATAL_CPUGFX
Description: CPUGFX_PWRGD timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_CPUCORE, V_GFXCORE (they can be low resistance, dont confuse with a short!), check R9C64, U9D2, U9D3, U9D4, U9E1, U9E2 drivers, 10 mosfets, surrounding resistors and U9C2.

Name: FATAL_V_5P0_I2C_UNREACHABLE
Description: U3E2 I2C unreachable -> Check surrounding traces, replace U3E2

Name: FATAL_GFXCPU_I2C_UNREACHABLE
Description: NCP4204 I2C unreachable -> Check R9C1, R9C2, surrounding traces, replace U9C2

Name: FATAL_MEMIOAB
Description: U9F2 I2C unreachable -> Check surrounding traces, replace U9F2

Name: FATAL_MEMIOCD
Description: U6C1 I2C unreachable -> Check surrounding traces, replace U6C1

Name: FATAL_V12_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly, check powersupply. 12V unstable, maybe V_EXT (R5R20, R5R19), check PSU_V12P0_EN (R9A2, R9B2)

Name: FATAL_V5_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly, check powersupply. Unstable V_5P0, check C3E15.

Name: FATAL_PWRGPA_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly, VREG_PWRGPA_PWRGD went low while console was on, V_3P3, V_SOC1P8PLL, VMEMIOAB/CD, VTT[ABCD] unstable. Check C4F21, C9E11 and C6C14.

Name: FATAL_SBPOWERUP2_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly, SBPOWERUP2 failed while console is on, unstable

Name: FATAL_PWRGPB_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly, VREG_PWRGPB_PWRGD went low while console was on, V_FUSE, V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE or V_MEMCORE unstable. Check C6F9, C6F12 and C6E15.

Name: FATAL_CPUGFX_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly, CPUGFX_PWRGD went low while console was on. Check output filtering C8D1, C8D2, C8D4, C8E1, C8E5, C8E8, C8E10. General corrosion / timing problem in NCP area?

Name: FATAL_NBCORE
Description: U5F3 I2C unreachable -> Check surrounding traces, replace U5F3

Name: BOOT_SBUNRESETWAIT
Description: V_SB2P5, V_SB1P1, V_SB1P8 timeout, unable to unreset southbridge. Check short on V_SB2P5, V_SB1P1, V_SB1P8, replace U3D3, U3E1 or U3D5 or surrounding resistors, southbridge

Name: BOOT_PSPBOOTACKWAIT_DONE
Description: Waiting for PSP Boot Acknowledge finished, APU <-> SB communication failed on SMBUS3, no PSP boot acknowledge, check R4D31, R4D38. V_FUSE/V_SOC1P8 unavailable, check resistance and voltage on both, if missing U5C3 or U6D1 related. Cause can be APU not receiving PWROK from SB (Check R5R5, R5R6), Check V_SOC1P8VDD (FB6D1), reball APU, APU.

Name: BOOT_PSPPORSPEWWAIT_DONE
Description: PSP Power-On Reset spew wait done, unable to unreset APU, APU stuck in reset -> Check R5R9, R5T10, reball APU, APU.

Name: BOOT_XSS_TIMEOUT_46
Description: XSS wait timeout (SOC not responding) - error fallback 0xeb46 right AFTER 0x007x - VTT[ABCD]/V_Memio timeout, check resistances & voltage. 0xeb46 right AFTER 0x045x - APU <-> VRM CONTROLLER SVI2 communication attempt failed. Check R9C4, R2R2, R2R3, replace ncp, reball APU, APU.

Name: BOOT_XSS_TIMEOUT_47
Description: XSS wait timeout fallback path (word_20000090 nonzero)

Name: BOOT_COND_EARLY_ABORT
Description: Conditional POST on XSSActiveWait() return < 0 - XSS wait failed - early abort

Name: BOOT_FAIL_UNKNOWN
Description: seen with V_3P3_ENET short, late V3P3 shutdown or low?

Name: RESET_PSPACK_MISSING
Description: Unexpected PSP Boot Ack not received

Name: RESET_FATAL_THERMAL_PENDING
Description: Fatal or thermal error pending during wait

Name: RESET_PIM_BOOT_INCOMPLETE
Description: PIM boot ack or early boot signal incomplete

Name: RUNTIME
Description: Happens if sub_10001532 fails after repeated attempts maybe Timeout waiting for PCIe device

Name: RUNTIME
Description: PLL_Clk_Maybe() failed, likely clock not stable

Name: RUNTIME_EXTPOST
Description: General Error - Often byproduct, low priority

Name: RUNTIME_05
Description: General Error - Often byproduct, low priority

Name: RUNTIME_06
Description: General Error - Often byproduct, low priority

Name: RUNTIME_GET_SBSystemSubmode
Description: Final PCIe init or handshake failure

Name: RUNTIME_I2C_CLEARMSG
Description: I2C bus failed to clear. Pi pico hickup, check all I2C devices (Frontpanel, U5F3, U3E2, U6C1, U9C2, U9F2), southbridge.

Name: 2BL_PSQ_MISSMATCH
Description: Possible EMMC corruption, thrown when not matching firmware version in EMMC

Name: THERMAL_22
Description: APU to SB: Thermal trip -> Check R5R8, R5R7, traces, reball southbridge or apu, apu tempsensor fault. Is the console just overheating?

Name: MEMORY_OG
Description: General memory error (MEM <-> APU), check V_Memio / VTT A-D resistances&voltages, check resistors around rams, replace rams (ZQ method?), reball apu.

Name: FATAL_V12
Description: V_12P0_GATED not available / not detected / timeout. -> Check short on V_12P0_GATED, check V_EXT (R5T18, R5T26), Q9D1, R9C24, Q1P2

Name: FATAL_PWRGPA
Description: PWRGPA timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check U9F1, R6T4, Q9F1, Q9F2, surrounding resistors/capacitors. V_Memio or V_VTTB short ?

Name: FATAL_PWRGPB
Description: PWRGPB timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE (can be low resistance, dont confuse with a short!). Pull VREG_PWRGPB_EN to V_3P3STBY manually and check V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE voltages. R5U9, U5F5, U5F3, Q6F1, Q6F2, surrounding caps and resistors.

Name: FATAL_CPUGFX
Description: CPUGFX_PWRGD timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_CPUCORE, V_GFXCORE (overcurrentshutdown) (they can be low resistance, dont confuse with a short!), check drivers U9D2, U9E1, U9E2, all 6 mosfets, surrounding resistors and U9C2.

Name: FATAL_GFXCPU_I2C_UNREACHABLE
Description: NCP4204 I2C unreachable -> Check R9C29, R9C30, surrounding traces, check V_5P0_GATED available? (R9D30, Q8D1), replace U9C2

Name: FATAL_V12_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly. -> V_12P0_GATED failed while on, check V_EXT (R5T18, R5T26), Q9D1, R9C24, check powersupply

Name: FATAL_HW_FAILURE_OLD5
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly. Ignore

Name: FATAL_PWRGPA_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly. PWGRPA failed while on, check output capacitors for V_Memio (C9E8).

Name: FATAL_SBPOWERUP2_HW_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly. SBPOWERUP2 failed while console is on, unstable

Name: FATAL_PWRGPB_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly. PWGRPB failed while on, check output capacitors for V_SOCPHY (C5F5, C5F6), V_NBCORE (C5E10, C5E11).

Name: FATAL_CPUGFX_FAILURE
Description: Thrown when console unplugged unexpectedly. CPUGFX_PWRGD failed while on, check output capacitors for V_CPUCORE, V_GFXCORE (C8D1, C8D2, C8D3, C8E1, C8E2, C8E3)

Name: FATAL_NBCORE
Description: U5F3 I2C unreachable -> Check surrounding traces, replace U5F3

Name: BOOT_SBUNRESETWAIT
Description: V_SB1P1, V_SB1P8 timeout, unable to unreset southbridge. Check short on V_SB1P1, V_SB1P8, check U3E1 or U3F1 or surrounding resistors

Name: BOOT_PSPBOOTACKWAIT_DONE
Description: APU <-> SB communication failed on SMBUS3, no PSP boot acknowledge (R3T1, R3T2, R5T5, R5T6, R4E29, R4E28), can be caused by: V_FUSE/V_SOC1P8 unavailable -> Check R5D10, U5D3, R5D9, D5D2, D5D1, R5R11, R5R10, U5D2, R6D6, R5D6, seen with low V3P3, possible V_3P3_ENET short. Can be APU not receiving PWROK from SB (Check R5T29, R5T28)Check V_SOC1P8VDD (FB6D1), reball APU, APU.

Name: BOOT_PSPPORSPEWWAIT_DONE
Description: PSP Power-On Reset spew wait done, unable to unreset APU, APU stuck in reset -> Check R5T31, R5T13, APU.

Name: BOOT_XSS_TIMEOUT_46
Description: XSS wait timeout (SOC not responding) - error fallback 0xeb46 right AFTER 0x007x - VTT[ABCD]/V_Memio timeout, check resistances & voltage. 0xeb46 right AFTER 0x04c5 - V3P3 unavailable, check short, check U5D4, C5D5, R9C31, R5D11, R5D13. 0xeb46 right AFTER 0x045x - APU <-> VRM CONTROLLER SVI2 communication attempt failed. check resistance on all apu rails, can show partial dead core (V_Memio?). Check R9D3, R2R2, R2R1, R9C23, R1P21, replace ncp, APU.

Name: BOOT_XSS_TIMEOUT_47
Description: XSS wait timeout fallback path (word_20000090 nonzero)

Description: APU to SB: Thermal trip -> Can be caused by missing V_SOC1P8, check U5D2, R6D6, R5D6. Check R5T27, R5T3, R5E12, R5T7, R5E11, U5E2, R5E9, R5E8, R5T42, apu tempsensor fault. Is the apu just too hot?
